  109. ‌  type t = {

  117. ‌  let get_index t h = (h land max_int) mod (Array.length t.table)

  119. ‌  let limit = 7

  122. ‌  let create sz =
  123.     let sz = if sz < 7 then 7 else sz in
  124. ‌    let sz = if sz > Sys.max_array_length then Sys.max_array_length else sz in
  125.     {
  126.       table = Array.make sz emptybucket;
  127.       hashes = Array.make sz [| |];
  128.       limit = limit;
  129.       oversize = 0;

  133. ‌  let clear t =
  134.     for i = 0 to Array.length t.table - 1 do
  135.       t.table.(i) <- emptybucket;
  136.       t.hashes.(i) <- [| |];
  137.     done;

  139.     t.oversize <- 0


  142. ‌  let fold f t init =
  143.     let rec fold_bucket i b accu =
  144.       if i >= length b then accu else
  145.       match get b i with
  146.       | Some v -> fold_bucket (i+1) b (f v accu)
  147.       | None -> fold_bucket (i+1) b accu
  148.     in
  149.     Array.fold_right (fold_bucket 0) t.table init


  152. ‌  let iter f t =
  153.     let rec iter_bucket i b =
  154.       if i >= length b then () else
  155.       match get b i with
  156.       | Some v -> f v; iter_bucket (i+1) b
  157.       | None -> iter_bucket (i+1) b
  158.     in
  159.     Array.iter (iter_bucket 0) t.table


  162. ‌  let iter_weak f t =
  163.     let rec iter_bucket i j b =
  164.       if i >= length b then () else
  165.       match check b i with
  166.       | true -> f b t.hashes.(j) i; iter_bucket (i+1) j b
  167.       | false -> iter_bucket (i+1) j b
  168.     in
  169.     Array.iteri (iter_bucket 0) t.table


  172. ‌  let rec count_bucket i b accu =
  173.     if i >= length b then accu else
  174.     count_bucket (i+1) b (accu + (if check b i then 1 else 0))


  177. ‌  let count t =
  178.     Array.fold_right (count_bucket 0) t.table 0


  181. ‌  let next_sz n = Int.min (3 * n / 2 + 3) Sys.max_array_length
  182. ‌  let prev_sz n = ((n - 3) * 2 + 2) / 3

  184. ‌  let test_shrink_bucket t =
  185.     let bucket = t.table.(t.rover) in
  186.     let hbucket = t.hashes.(t.rover) in
  187.     let len = length bucket in
  188.     let prev_len = prev_sz len in
  189.     let live = count_bucket 0 bucket 0 in
  190.     if live <= prev_len then begin
  191.       let rec loop i j =
  192.         if j >= prev_len then begin
  193.           if check bucket i then loop (i + 1) j
  194.           else if check bucket j then begin
  195.             blit bucket j bucket i 1;
  196.             hbucket.(i) <- hbucket.(j);
  197.             loop (i + 1) (j - 1);
  198.           end else loop i (j - 1);
  199.         end;
  200.       in
  201.       loop 0 (length bucket - 1);
  202.       if prev_len = 0 then begin
  203.         t.table.(t.rover) <- emptybucket;
  204.         t.hashes.(t.rover) <- [| |];
  205.       end else begin
  206. ‌        let newbucket = weak_create prev_len in
  207.         blit bucket 0 newbucket 0 prev_len;
  208.         t.table.(t.rover) <- newbucket;
  209.         t.hashes.(t.rover) <- Array.sub hbucket 0 prev_len
  210.       end;
  211.       if len > t.limit && prev_len <= t.limit then t.oversize <- t.oversize - 1;
  212.     end;
  213.     t.rover <- (t.rover + 1) mod (Array.length t.table)


  216. ‌  let rec resize t =
  217.     let oldlen = Array.length t.table in
  218.     let newlen = next_sz oldlen in
  219.     if newlen > oldlen then begin
  220.       let newt = create newlen in
  221.       let add_weak ob oh oi =
  222.         let setter nb ni _ = blit ob oi nb ni 1 in
  223.         let h = oh.(oi) in
  224.         add_aux newt setter None h (get_index newt h);
  225.       in
  226.       iter_weak add_weak t;
  227.       t.table <- newt.table;
  228.       t.hashes <- newt.hashes;
  229.       t.limit <- newt.limit;
  230.       t.oversize <- newt.oversize;
  231.       t.rover <- t.rover mod Array.length newt.table;
  232.     end else begin
  233.       t.limit <- max_int;             (* maximum size already reached *)
  234.       t.oversize <- 0;
  235.     end

  237.   and add_aux t setter d h index =
  238.     let bucket = t.table.(index) in
  239.     let hashes = t.hashes.(index) in
  240.     let sz = length bucket in
  241.     let rec loop i =
  242.       if i >= sz then begin
  243.         let newsz =
  244.           Int.min (3 * sz / 2 + 3) (Sys.max_array_length - additional_values)
  245.         in
  246.         if newsz <= sz then failwith "Weak.Make: hash bucket cannot grow more";
  247.         let newbucket = weak_create newsz in
  248.         let newhashes = Array.make newsz 0 in
  249.         blit bucket 0 newbucket 0 sz;
  250.         Array.blit hashes 0 newhashes 0 sz;
  251.         setter newbucket sz d;
  252.         newhashes.(sz) <- h;
  253.         t.table.(index) <- newbucket;
  254.         t.hashes.(index) <- newhashes;
  255.         if sz <= t.limit && newsz > t.limit then begin
  256.           t.oversize <- t.oversize + 1;
  257.           for _i = 0 to over_limit do test_shrink_bucket t done;
  258.         end;
  259.         if t.oversize > Array.length t.table / over_limit then resize t;
  260.       end else if check bucket i then begin
  261.         loop (i + 1)
  262.       end else begin
  263.         setter bucket i d;
  264.         hashes.(i) <- h;
  265.       end;
  266.     in
  267.     loop 0


  270. ‌  let add t d =
  271.     let h = H.hash d in
  272.     add_aux t set (Some d) h (get_index t h)

  274.   (* General auxiliary function for searching for a particular value
  275.    * in a hash-set, and acting according to whether or not it's found *)

  277. ‌  let find_aux t d found notfound =
  278.     let h = H.hash d in
  279.     let index = get_index t h in
  280.     let bucket = t.table.(index) in
  281.     let hashes = t.hashes.(index) in
  282.     let sz = length bucket in
  283.     let rec loop i =
  284.       if i >= sz then notfound h index
  285.       else if h = hashes.(i) then begin
  286.         match get bucket i with
  287.         | Some v as opt when H.equal v d -> found bucket i opt v
  288.         | _ -> loop (i + 1)
  289.       end else loop (i + 1)
  290.     in
  291.     loop 0

  293. ‌  let find_opt t d = find_aux t d (fun _b _i  o _v -> o)
  294.                                   (fun _h _i -> None)

  296.   let merge t d    = find_aux t d (fun _b _i _o  v -> v)
  297.                                   (fun  h  i ->
  298.                                         add_aux t set (Some d) h i; d)

  300.   let find t d     = find_aux t d (fun _b _i _o  v -> v)
  301.                                   (fun _h _i -> raise Not_found)

  303.   let remove t d   = find_aux t d (fun  b  i _o _v -> set b i None)
  304.                                   (fun _h _i -> ())

  306.   let mem t d      = find_aux t d (fun _b _i _o _v -> true)
  307.                                   (fun _h _i -> false)

  309.   let find_all t d =
  310.     let h = H.hash d in
  311. ‌    let index = get_index t h in
  312. ‌    let bucket = t.table.(index) in
  313. ‌    let hashes = t.hashes.(index) in
  314. ‌    let sz = length bucket in
  315. ‌    let rec loop i accu =
  316.       if i >= sz then accu
  317.       else if h = hashes.(i) then begin
  318.         match get bucket i with
  319.         | Some v when H.equal v d -> loop (i + 1) (v :: accu)
  320.         | _ -> loop (i + 1) accu
  321.       end else loop (i + 1) accu
  322.     in
  323.     loop 0 []

  325. ‌  let stats t =
  326.     let len = Array.length t.table in
  327.     let lens = Array.map length t.table in
  328.     Array.sort compare lens;
  329.     let totlen = Array.fold_left ( + ) 0 lens in
  330.     (len, count t, totlen, lens.(0), lens.(len/2), lens.(len-1))
